CatDescriptText: Cutline of article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 18, 1960, pg. 5 reads: "6. Wilhelmina Gray Cooper was the hostess with "the mostest" in one of the most frequented booths at the show. Naturally, it was the Metropolitan bottling Company's Pepsi-Cola"
